question.question: Find top 10 repositories by the most commented issues

sql:
SELECT
  repo_name,
  countIf(event_type = 'WatchEvent') AS star_count,
  any(issue_number) AS issue_number,
  any(issue_url) AS issue_url,
  max(comment_count) AS comment_count,
  max(unique_commenters) AS unique_commenters
FROM (
  SELECT
    repo_name,
    number AS issue_number,
    concat('https://github.com/', repo_name, '/issues/', toString(number)) AS issue_url,
    max(comments) AS comment_count,
    uniqExactIf(actor_login, event_type = 'IssueCommentEvent') AS unique_commenters
  FROM github_events
  WHERE
    event_type IN ('IssuesEvent', 'IssueCommentEvent')
    AND number > 10
    AND repo_name IN (
      SELECT repo_name
      FROM github_events
      WHERE event_type = 'WatchEvent'
      GROUP BY repo_name
      HAVING count() > 100
    )
  GROUP BY repo_name, number
  HAVING comment_count = max(comment_count) AND unique_commenters >= 10
)
ANY LEFT JOIN (
  SELECT
    repo_name,
    countIf(event_type = 'WatchEvent') AS star_count
  FROM github_events
  WHERE event_type = 'WatchEvent'
  GROUP BY repo_name
) USING repo_name
GROUP BY repo_name
ORDER BY star_count DESC
LIMIT 10

question.name: pipe_42.pipe
question.content:
DESCRIPTION >
    Top10 repos (with>100 stars) ranked by total stars; for each repo return the *single* issue (number>10) that has the most issue comments created (with >=10 unique commenters) along with its URL, comment count, unique authors, issue#, and the repos star count

NODE endpoint
SQL >
    SELECT
        concat('https://github.com/', repo_name, '/issues/', toString(number)) AS URL,
        max(comments),
        argMax(authors, comments) AS authors,
        argMax(number, comments) AS number,
        sum(stars) AS stars
    FROM
    (
        SELECT *
        FROM
        (
            SELECT
                repo_name,
                number,
                count() AS comments,
                uniq(actor_login) AS authors
            FROM github_events
            WHERE (event_type = 'IssueCommentEvent') AND (action = 'created') AND (number > 10)
            GROUP BY
                repo_name,
                number
            HAVING authors >= 10
        ) AS t1
        INNER JOIN
        (
            SELECT
                repo_name,
                count() AS stars
            FROM github_events
            WHERE event_type = 'WatchEvent'
            GROUP BY repo_name
            HAVING stars > 100
        ) AS t2 USING (repo_name)
    )
    GROUP BY repo_name
    ORDER BY stars DESC
    LIMIT 10

TYPE endpoint
